In [10]:
data['EDAD_2'] = np.nan

for i in range(data.shape[0]):
    if data['EDAD'][i] <20:
        data['EDAD_2'][i]=str(19)
    elif data['EDAD'][i] >60:
        data['EDAD_2'][i]=str(61)
    elif data['EDAD'].isnull()[i]==True:
        data['EDAD_2'][i]='NO REGISTRA'
    else:
        data['EDAD_2'][i]=str(data['EDAD'][i])

g=data[data['EDAD_2']!='NO REGISTRA']['EDAD_2'].to_list()
f=pd.cut(g, bins=np.arange(10,80,10), right=False)

y=list(f.value_counts().index)
x=list(f.value_counts().values)
x_p=list(np.round(f.value_counts().values/sum(f.value_counts().values),4)*100)

d=pd.DataFrame({'Age interval':y, 'Employees':x, '%':x_p})

d.plot(x='Age interval',y='%', kind='barh', colormap='PuBuGn_r', grid=True, legend=False)

for i in range(d.shape[0]):
    plt.text(d['%'][i]+2,i,str(round(d['%'][i],2))+'%',color='darkblue',size='medium',weight=1000)
plt.ylabel('Age interval')
plt.xlabel('Employees (%)')
plt.title('Employee age')
plt.xlim(0,115)

plt.show()
